      <div class="col-xs-8 col-xs-offset-2 banner-para">
        <p id="line-height">I'm a self confessed front end nerd, I'm passionate about making a site look as clean as possible and everything that goes along with that. Back when I was teaching skiing I used to claim that "if it looks good, it is good" and I maintain that mantra for web development.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="work-banner colored-banner">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <h1 id="white-font" class="text-center">Previous Work</h1>
      <div class="col-xs-4 col-xs-offset-2 work-examples">
        <%= image_tag "Voyagr-logo", height: 51, width: 215, class: "work-img" %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-4 col-xs-offset-2 work-examples">
        <%= image_tag "Fastgardener", height: 51, width: 215, class: "work-img" %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br>
    <div class="row work-descriptions">
      <div id="white-font" class="col-xs-5 col-xs-offset-1 text-center">
        <p>Voyagr is a facebook chatbot developed in just two weeks to showcase skills acquired at Le Wagon's coding bootcamp. It provides tailored travel suggestions based on the answers a user gives to a facebook quiz, alongside a couple of other features.</p>
      </div>
      <div id="white-font" class="col-xs-5 col-xs-offset-1 text-center">
        <p>Fast Gardener has been described as 'the uber for gardening' by Business Advice and Pro Gardener. It provides a fast and easy way to book a professional gardener, without trawling through reviews or waiting around for a reasonable quote. </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="responsive-banner">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">Mobile first design</h1>
    <div class="repsonsive-examples">
      <div class="responsive-example">
        <i class="devices fas fa-mobile"></i>
        <%= image_tag "Phone Screen", height: 180, width: 110, class: "device-pictures" %>
      </div>
      <div class="responsive-example">
        <i class="devices fas fa-tablet"></i>
        <%= image_tag "Ipad Screen", height: 180, width: 160, class: "device-pictures" %>
      </div>
      <div class="responsive-example">
        <i class="devices fas fa-tv"></i>
        <%= image_tag "Computer Screen Cropped", height: 160, width: 255, class: "device-pictures-computer" %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p id="line-height" class="mobile-para">Since late <%= link_to "2016", "http://gs.statcounter.com/press/mobile-and-tablet-internet-usage-exceeds-desktop-for-first-time-worldwide", target: "_blank", class: "voyagr" %>, worldwide mobile and tablet internet usage has exceeded desktop usage. This means that websites designed without mobile and tablet users in mind will be excluding over half of their potential audience. As such, my goal is to provide for this preponderant group first, ensuring that there is no loss of functionality or design as a result of varied device usage.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="about-banner colored-banner">
